<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="5" xml:id="C34.S7.SS3.p1.s1">
For recursion relations see Varshalovich et al. (1988, §10.5).
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
<subsection xml:id="C34.S7.SS4">
<title>Orthogonality</title>          
<para xml:id="C34.S7.SS4.p1">

<sentence sentence-num-in-para="1" sentence-num-in-section="6" xml:id="C34.S7.SS4.p1.s1">
 <Math equation-number="34.7.2" mode="display" xml:id="C34.S7.E2">\sum_{j_{12}\,j_{34}}(2j_{12}+1)(2j_{34}+1)(2j_{13}+1)(2j_{24}+1)\begin{ Bmatrix}j_{1}&amp;j_{2}&amp;j_{12}\\ j_{3}&amp;j_{4}&amp;j_{34}\\ j_{13}&amp;j_{24}&amp;j\end{Bmatrix}\begin{Bmatrix}j_{1}&amp;j_{2}&amp;j_{12}\\ j_{3}&amp;j_{4}&amp;j_{34}\\ j^{\prime}_{13}&amp;j^{\prime}_{24}&amp;j\end{Bmatrix}=\delta_{j_{13},j^{\prime}_{13}} \delta_{j_{24},j^{\prime}_{24}}</Math>.
</sentence>

</para>
 
</subsection>
 
